column2: ITP approved for use by: Pradeep Talasila
Acceptance Criteria - Precast supplier is required to provide the following Quality Assurance documentation for each element, typically this consists of:
i. Certificate of Compliance / Birth Certificate
viii. Record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate compliance with dimensional tolerances of precast and bearing plates
Note: Different revisions of 610 have different clause numbers
Collate: Precast Quality Assurance Documentation so it can be uploaded into Teambinder
Acceptance Criteria - Installation of Precast Plank WMS to be submitted for review to the Nominated Authority
Frequency - Once, 4 weeks prior to Instrallation of Precast Plank
Acceptance Criteria - Check the revision of the IFC drawings are current as per the drawing register (on Teambinder)
Frequency - Prior to starting Works and at regular intervals

Acceptance Criteria - Survey activities undertaken to ensure and validate that all Works meet level and location requirements within the tolerances as per the table 610.462 as applicable to the element.
Attach: Lot Map, Marked up drawing which shows the Lot Location and extent

Acceptance Criteria - The Falsework drawings submitted shall state all design assumptions and shall include a statement of the loads and any dimensional changes due to loading in all members of the falsework. The drawings shall be fully detailed including all member sizes and materials, dimensions, levels, erection procedures and other relevant details including bracing, connections and foundations, to ensure that erection and inspection of the falsework can be undertaken without reference to any other documentation.
Responsibility - Temporary Works Designer, Proof Engineer

Acceptance Criteria - The application of any permanent load shall not proceed until the signed Certificate of Compliance - Falsework Inspection of the constructed falsework has been reviewed and accepted by the Nominated Party.
Attach: Temporary Works Permit to Construct, Apply Load and Remove
Responsibility - Temporary Works Designer, Proof Engineer
Acceptance Criteria - Unless otherwise specified, precast elements shall be lifted using the lifting points provided and supported with the top surface uppermost at all times.

Acceptance Criteria - Precast elements shall be placed onto the bearings/bearing shims and not released from the crane until sufficiently braced in accordance with the approved temporary works design and/or IFC drawings.
○ The nominal gap between elements is as per the IFC Drawings.
Acceptance Criteria - All manufactured precast elements shall be traced from the completion of manufacture to their final location by a unique identification number.
Record: The final location of each precast element, showing individual ID and date installed onto the Red-line Drawings or Survey Report
5.6 - Platform and Stitch Pours between Planks
Acceptance Criteria - Precast elements shall be stitched together, either by the Stitches or by the Platform pours. Related Stitch and Platform Structrual Concrete Lots to be closed out.
Verifying Documents - This ITP / Structural Concrete ITP
Acceptance Criteria - Provide record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate concrete members comply with specified tolerances.
Acceptance Criteria - Ensure that any NCRs pertaining to the lot / element / Work area that this ITP covers, have been closed in CAMs.
Frequency - Once, prior to closure of this lot / element / Work area

On behalf of Metropolitan Roads Program Alliance, it is hereby certified that the Works represented by the item of work listed have been tested in accordance with the Project Quality Plan and conform in all respects with the requirements of the Contract.
